0Current Usings:  (CP,R11) (CV,R12)

0                                   8368              ¿þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþÜ
                                    8369              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    8370              Ÿ  LINEMOD -- Routine to do modify/edit processing on a line.         Ÿ
                                    8371              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    8372              Ÿ   On entry:                                                         Ÿ
                                    8373              Ÿ     CPLCNO - lineno of line to modify                               Ÿ
                                    8374              Ÿ     R1,R0 - line loc, len                                           Ÿ
                                    8375              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    8376              Ÿ   On exit:                                                          Ÿ
                                    8377              Ÿ     CPLCNO - lineno (past splits, etc.)                             Ÿ
                                    8378              Ÿ     R1,R0 - modified line loc, len                                  Ÿ
                                    8379              Ÿ     R15 (and CC):                                                   Ÿ
                                    8380              Ÿ        0 - modificiation completed                                  Ÿ
                                    8381              Ÿ        4 - modification aborted (attn)                              Ÿ
                                    8382              Ÿ       -4 - terminate command ($attn)                                Ÿ
                                    8383              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    8384              Ÿ   Notes:  CPMODNEX is set by the caller to tell LINEMOD the         Ÿ
                                    8385              Ÿ     lineno of the next line (although, it does not exist            Ÿ
                                    8386              Ÿ     when the routine is called).  Then if a split, collect, etc.    Ÿ
                                    8387              Ÿ     is done LINEMOD won't go past that lineno.  If "CPMODNEX"       Ÿ
                                    8388              Ÿ     is zero, LINEMOD will use the next existing lineno.             Ÿ
                                    8389              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                    8390              Ÿ     METLINER is the lineno of the original line being modified      Ÿ
                                    8391              Ÿ     or the last split/collect lineno.  It is not updated when       Ÿ
                                    8392              Ÿ     the user uses the ".line x" function to modify a different      Ÿ
                                    8393              Ÿ     line.  CPLCNO is set to METLINER just before exiting to         Ÿ
                                    8394              Ÿ     allow the caller to continue any range after that line.         Ÿ
                                    8395              Ÿ                                                                     Ÿ
                                                      ¾þþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþþ»

0                                  32819              *
                                   32820              *
                                   32821              *   CHANGE COMMAND
                                   32822              *
                                   32823              *
                                   32824              *   THE CODE IS DIVIDED INTO BASICALLY 2 PARTS:
                                   32825              *     1. WE SCAN ALL THE VARIOUS OPTIONS.  VERY MINIMAL PROCESSING
                                   32826              *        IS DONE ON THESE OPTIONS. MOSTLY THEY ARE JUST STORED AWAY
                                   32827              *        IN THE LOCAL CHANGE WORK AREA.  WE THEN CALL THE RANGE
                                   32828              *        PROCESSOR.
                                   32829              *     2. THE RANGE PROCESSOR CO-ROUTINE. THIS ROUTINE (AND
                                   32830              *        SUBROUTINES) DO ALL THE ACTUAL LINE CHANGEING. THESE
                                   32831              *        ROUTINES ALSO USE THE LOCAL CHANGE WORK AREA. FOR
                                   32832              *        CHANGE ALGORITHMS SEE THE CO-ROUTINE CODE AND
                                   32833              *        SUBROUTINES.
                                   32834              *
                                   32835              *
 006636 50E0 D000/9008_      00000 32836              CHANGE   XPROC CHWA
 USING  *,R7
 USING  CHWA-(4+36),R8

                                   32888                       COMMENT                   EMERGENCY ZAP LOCATION **

                                   44313              *
                                   44314              *  DO FINAL PROCESSING OF CHANGED LINE,,,
                                   44315              *   AND WRITE CHANGED LINE.
                                   44316              *
                                   44317              *  THE MAIN JOB OF THIS ROUTINE IS TO WRITE OUT THE
                                   44318              *  CHANGED LINE TO THE ACTIVE FILE.
                                   44319              *
                                   44320              *  THIS CODE COPIED FROM OLD VERSION OF CHANGE COMMAND.
                                   44321              *  THERE ARE MANY ODDS AND ENDS ADDED TO MAKE THE USER
                                   44322              *  INTERFACE NICE. (AND THE CODE A BIT COMPLICATED.)

                                   44325              *  PAGE MODE INTERFACE, VERIFY, ETC... SO THIS IS MORE OR
